- [Whistle Blows]
- [Section Leader] Do not slow it down on me.

19:58.239 --> 20:01.908
Move it! Move it!
Come on. Come on. Pick it up!

20:01.993 --> 20:04.578
- [Band Chanting]
- ♪♪ [Drums]

20:07.039 --> 20:11.418
"The beginning is always today."
One of my favorite quotes.

20:11.502 --> 20:14.504
President Wagner,
what a pleasant surprise.

20:14.589 --> 20:18.383
So what exciting, new beginnings
can we look forward to this year?

20:18.467 --> 20:20.385
Well, for the most part...

20:20.469 --> 20:23.930
I'll continue with
the overall direction of the program.

20:24.015 --> 20:25.891
That direction is a losing one.

20:25.975 --> 20:28.184
I don't think we can measure
the success of our program...

20:28.269 --> 20:30.520
by the number of people
shaking their butts in the stands.

20:30.605 --> 20:32.898
And no, we didn't win
the B.E.T. Classic.

20:32.982 --> 20:37.193
But our first obligation
is to educate, and then entertain.

20:37.278 --> 20:41.656
Please, not the edu-tainment speech, James.
Save it for your students.

20:41.741 --> 20:45.744
It's a good one.
The kids in my program are learning.

20:45.828 --> 20:50.123
There won't be a program if thee alumni continue to lose interest.

20:50.207 --> 20:52.167
We win, they write checks.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.628
Dr. Henderson was smart enough
to know that.

20:54.712 --> 20:56.755
He played popular music.

20:56.839 --> 21:01.009
That was James Brown and Marvin Gaye,
not the "Thong Song."

21:01.093 --> 21:05.138
Now, I will play popular music,
but not at the expense of musicianship.

21:05.222 --> 21:07.724
When you hired me, you wanted me
to strive for excellence...

21:07.808 --> 21:09.935
and that is exactly
what I am doing.

21:10.019 --> 21:13.939
I also said we needed to win.

21:14.023 --> 21:16.024
[Buck Wild]
One, two.

21:16.108 --> 21:18.944
One, two!

21:19.028 --> 21:21.529
One, two! One—

21:21.614 --> 21:23.573
[Dr. Lee]
Freeze!

21:23.658 --> 21:26.409
I want your knees
hitting your chest.

21:26.494 --> 21:29.704
Then drive your feet
into the ground.

21:29.789 --> 21:33.208
I'll say it again.
Knees into chest!

21:33.292 --> 21:36.378
Then feet hit the ground!

21:36.462 --> 21:38.672
Buck Wild!

21:38.756 --> 21:40.799
When I say, "chest,"
you say, "out."

21:40.883 --> 21:43.009
- Chest! Chest!
- [All] Out! Out!

21:43.094 --> 21:46.054
[Buck Wild] What's wrong with your chest?
Your chest don't come out?

21:46.138 --> 21:50.850
- What's wrong with his chest?
Stick your chests out!
- Damn.

21:50.935 --> 21:52.519
- Chest! Chest!
- Out! Out!

21:52.603 --> 21:55.146
- Chest! Chest!
- Out! Out!

21:55.231 --> 21:59.442
[Laila] One, two, three and four,
five and six and seven and eight.

21:59.527 --> 22:02.320
- ♪♪ [Hip-hop]
- And one, two, three, four...

22:02.405 --> 22:04.614
five, six, seven.

22:04.699 --> 22:06.992
Come on. Let's go.

22:14.917 --> 22:17.460
I'm sorry, but, um,
rehearsals are closed.

22:17.545 --> 22:19.587
I didn't know you was a dancer.

22:19.672 --> 22:23.425
- Do I know you?
- [Scoffs] What, you don't know?

22:23.509 --> 22:26.594
Dr. Lee sent me over,
you know, to check on things.

22:26.679 --> 22:30.432
- To check on things?
- Yeah. See, they got this hot new snare drummer.

22:30.516 --> 22:32.851
Real good-lookin' brother
with cornrows.

22:32.935 --> 22:36.229
Yeah, he about to bring it
like you ain't never heard.

22:36.313 --> 22:39.274
See, I can help you out
with a couple of them dance moves.

22:39.358 --> 22:41.735
- One, two, three. Pop it. Take it.
- [Laughs]

22:41.819 --> 22:44.404
Drop it. Yeah.

22:44.488 --> 22:46.489
Beat it, Devon.

22:47.533 --> 22:50.452
Thought you ain't remember me.

22:50.536 --> 22:54.789
[Iron Man]
A break is five minutes, not 15.

22:56.292 --> 22:58.376
Hey, Devon,
you know if you keep messin' up...

22:58.461 --> 23:02.338
- Ernest actually might get a chest.
- [Men Laughing]

23:02.423 --> 23:06.926
[Straining] And Diedre might get
strong enough to pick up a hot comb.

23:07.011 --> 23:09.012
[Men Laughing]

23:09.096 --> 23:12.098
♪♪ [Rhythmic Drumming]

23:14.310 --> 23:16.936
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hold up. Hold up.

23:17.021 --> 23:19.272
What are y'all lookin' at?

23:19.356 --> 23:22.609
Drums ain't goin' nowhere,
so what you clowns lookin' down for?

23:22.693 --> 23:25.278
Always remember this.

23:25.362 --> 23:28.531
Playin' the drums,
it's like makin' love.

23:28.616 --> 23:32.577
You can't be lookin' down there seein'
what's going' on, trying to get the flow right.

23:33.746 --> 23:36.998
Eyes on me.
Don't look down.

23:40.419 --> 23:43.463
Yeah. Now, when you
makin' love right...

23:43.547 --> 23:46.382
when you handlin' your business,
you feel it!

23:46.467 --> 23:48.718
- [Sticks Clatter]
- [Groans]

23:48.803 --> 23:51.346
Maybe you don't.

23:53.766 --> 23:55.934
Eyes on me.

23:58.187 --> 24:00.897
Mm-hmm!

24:00.981 --> 24:04.943
Yeah. You know how it is
when you hittin' that spot, right?

24:05.027 --> 24:06.611
- Don't ya, girl?
- [Sticks Clatter]

24:09.073 --> 24:12.117
Never look down.

24:31.887 --> 24:34.430
[Sticks Clatter]

24:34.515 --> 24:37.141
[Dr. Lee]
That was impressive.

24:37.226 --> 24:40.144
Thank you, sir.

24:40.229 --> 24:42.146
What I like most...

24:42.231 --> 24:44.524
was instead of
making Sean look bad...

24:44.608 --> 24:48.111
you made yourself
look like a jackass.

24:48.195 --> 24:50.947
Let's take this from the top,
and this time, follow me.

25:02.418 --> 25:04.419
Don't look down,
remember?

25:14.305 --> 25:17.682
You have to learn to follow
before you can lead, Mr. Miles.

26:09.026 --> 26:10.944
[Sean]
Congratulations.

26:11.028 --> 26:13.655
You're not crabs anymore.

26:13.739 --> 26:15.698
Now you're crab drummers.

26:15.783 --> 26:18.534
- [Murmuring]
- And tomorrow...

26:18.619 --> 26:21.955
it's tree-shaking
eliminations...

26:22.039 --> 26:25.583
which will determine
who will become A&T drummers.

26:26.961 --> 26:30.880
So tonight, celebrate...

26:30.965 --> 26:33.299
'cause you made it
through training.

26:33.384 --> 26:36.469
- [Cheering]
- Yo, whoa, whoa.

26:36.553 --> 26:40.056
After you prove a thorough knowledge
of the rule book.

26:40.140 --> 26:44.811
What is mandatory
of all A&T musicians?

26:44.895 --> 26:47.897
All A&T musicians
must read music.

26:47.982 --> 26:51.067
When can a P2 or P3...

26:51.151 --> 26:53.653
challenge for a spot
on the field?

26:53.737 --> 26:56.531
At the practice
before the performance, sir.

26:58.450 --> 27:00.451
What is...

27:03.539 --> 27:06.249
the last rule
of the rule book?

27:07.251 --> 27:09.168
Uh—

27:09.253 --> 27:12.255
[Mouthing Words]

27:15.676 --> 27:17.885
Head, uh—

27:20.514 --> 27:22.598
Stay ahead of the game.

27:22.683 --> 27:26.227
- [All Groan]
- [Man Imitates Buzzer Sounding]

27:28.147 --> 27:33.401
One band, one sound means
you all are responsible for each other.

27:33.485 --> 27:37.488
That means all of you are responsible
for showing Boyz n the Hood here...

27:37.573 --> 27:39.490
what the last rule is.

27:39.575 --> 27:42.035
[All Laugh]

27:44.038 --> 27:46.748
- What y'all laughing at?
- [Charles] It's on.

27:46.832 --> 27:50.418
Down, boy! Sit down!
Sit down!

27:50.502 --> 27:53.880
- What's up? I'm going to get
a lap dance or something?
- Something like that.

27:53.964 --> 27:57.592
- [Sean] Why don't you read
the last page, brother?
- All right, all right.

27:57.676 --> 27:59.927
"If you do not read
this rule book"—

28:00.012 --> 28:03.181
[All]
"Your head will be shaved."

28:03.265 --> 28:05.391
I told you to read the book.
I told you, dog.

28:05.476 --> 28:08.227
Devon, would you like me
to help you take your cornrows out?

28:08.312 --> 28:10.897
Would you like me
to help you take yours out?

28:10.981 --> 28:12.899
[Ernest]
Show you some love, dog.

28:12.983 --> 28:15.902
Hey, Dev, let me tell you.
You can look like me...

28:15.986 --> 28:19.405
- but you ain't never gonna play like me.
- [Razor Buzzing]

28:19.490 --> 28:22.033
[All Moaning]

28:22.117 --> 28:25.286
Watch my nerves.

28:25.370 --> 28:29.332
- You ain't touching my head.
- You don't follow the rules, you don't audition.

28:29.416 --> 28:32.960
Whatever, man.

28:33.045 --> 28:35.171
Is that what you want me
to tell Dr. Lee?

28:35.255 --> 28:39.050
I don't care what you tell him.
Dr. Lee ain't my daddy. This is bullshit.

28:39.134 --> 28:42.470
[Man]
Devon, come on, man.

28:44.473 --> 28:46.557
Man, how much fish is Charles
gonna put in there?

28:46.642 --> 28:49.435
He gonna short out
the whole building. Damn!

28:49.520 --> 28:52.522
♪♪ [Hip-hop]

28:54.566 --> 28:57.401
You know, uh, big brother Sean
is going to be really happy...

28:57.486 --> 29:01.030
when he finds out you quit the band
'cause of some stupid haircut.

29:01.115 --> 29:03.116
[Scoffs]

29:05.119 --> 29:08.204
Well, all right.

29:08.288 --> 29:11.749
I'm about to go get up
on some honeys.

29:11.834 --> 29:13.835
Holler!

29:18.507 --> 29:21.175
- [People Chattering]
- ♪♪ [Hip-hop Continues]

29:21.260 --> 29:24.428
This is the best.
Yo, yo, yo!

29:34.064 --> 29:36.858
[Man]
That's Devon.

29:39.403 --> 29:41.988
[All Cheering]

29:44.449 --> 29:47.076
Move away! I got my homeboy
right down the middle.

29:47.161 --> 29:51.122
Wait, wait, wait. Hold up. Hold up.
Who in here can do an uptown fade?

29:51.206 --> 29:54.041
- [All Yelling]
- I got this. I got this one.

29:54.126 --> 29:56.335
[Dr. Lee]
All right, crabs, check up!

29:56.420 --> 29:59.380
Tree-shaking is gonna
rank you P1 through P4.

29:59.464 --> 30:04.427
But only P1 s are guaranteed
a spot on the field.

30:04.511 --> 30:08.097
Now, if you’re a P2 or a P3,
you can still get a spot...

30:08.182 --> 30:11.350
in sections that are available,
so do your best.

30:11.435 --> 30:13.728
I'll see you all
on the other side.

30:20.903 --> 30:25.198
[Car Horn Honks Three Times]

30:25.282 --> 30:27.200
[Man]
Who is that?

30:27.284 --> 30:28.951
That's the upperclassmen.

30:29.036 --> 30:31.954
They flash their lights to say
what ranking they think we should get.

30:33.540 --> 30:35.458
Hey, Charles,
what's up with your socks?

30:35.542 --> 30:39.337
Man, don't worry about my socks, man.
It's a tuba thing, shorty.

30:39.421 --> 30:42.256
Better be.

30:47.512 --> 30:51.974
Mr. Miles, please play the required piece.
It's on the stand.

31:11.203 --> 31:13.955
You notice this crab hasn't looked down
at his sheet music once?

31:14.039 --> 31:16.207
- So?
- So?

31:16.291 --> 31:18.501
Who memorizes an audition piece?

31:18.585 --> 31:21.003
It's complicated.

31:21.088 --> 31:23.673
It's supposed to be read.
They expect you to stumble through it.

31:23.757 --> 31:26.300
Like you did?

31:49.241 --> 31:53.995
Mr. Miles, I guess you
didn't like the required piece as written.

31:54.079 --> 31:58.165
No, I just thought I'd add
a little something-something on the end.

32:02.671 --> 32:06.882
He can play. We all know that.
But his attitude is messed up.

32:06.967 --> 32:09.176
Now, I've put three years
into building this line.

32:09.261 --> 32:12.263
And the chemistry's great
and I don't want to jeopardize that.

32:12.347 --> 32:14.515
[Car Horns Honk Once]

32:17.811 --> 32:20.062
Your line seems
to think otherwise.

32:36.788 --> 32:40.499
[Excited Chattering]

32:40.584 --> 32:43.794
Yeah! P2 bass! Ow!

32:48.425 --> 32:50.718
[Devon's Voice]
I did it, Ma.

32:50.802 --> 32:53.179
Yeah, P1 and everything.

32:53.263 --> 32:55.765
The only freshman to do that.

32:55.849 --> 32:58.976
I was just calling to let you know
everything is everything.

32:59.061 --> 33:01.187
Come on.
You know what that means.

33:01.271 --> 33:04.273
Yeah, it's all good.

33:15.285 --> 33:18.454
Excuse me. Hi.

33:18.538 --> 33:21.791
I'm looking for this really good-looking
brother with cornrows.

33:21.875 --> 33:23.793
- And I heard—
- [Student] Shh!

33:23.877 --> 33:26.045
I heard he made the drumline.

33:26.129 --> 33:28.047
Oh, so now you got jokes?

33:28.131 --> 33:30.925
- [Chuckles] Congratulations.
- Thanks.

33:31.009 --> 33:33.969
You know I can't wait
to see you move to my beats.

33:34.054 --> 33:37.932
Do women actually respond
to the way you come at them?

33:40.310 --> 33:43.062
Well, actually,
they usually come at me.

33:43.146 --> 33:45.731
Hmm.

33:45.816 --> 33:48.109
What? Wait.
Where you going?

33:49.152 --> 33:51.153
My bad. Hold on.

33:53.573 --> 33:57.118
Why don't you school me
on how to come at a sister?

33:59.579 --> 34:01.288
Okay.

34:01.373 --> 34:05.626
How about showing some interest
in something other than the way she looks?

34:05.710 --> 34:08.129
All right.
Let me see what you got here.

34:08.213 --> 34:10.755
Damn, girl! What, you part
of Oprah's book club?

34:10.841 --> 34:14.092
I'm a philosophy major.

34:14.177 --> 34:16.762
- Dang. Philosophy? That's deep.
- Yeah.

34:16.847 --> 34:19.598
Like, Miss S.A.T. girl,
huh?

34:19.683 --> 34:23.143
Your parents probably used to put
all your report cards on the refrigerator.

34:23.228 --> 34:26.605
Mom be talking about,
"Aw, look, my baby done got another 'A.'

34:26.690 --> 34:28.440
Yes, she did."

34:28.525 --> 34:31.110
Something like that.
What about you?

34:31.194 --> 34:34.737
- What major makes your parents proud?
- Hey, to tell you the truth...

34:34.822 --> 34:37.449
I never even thought I'd be in college
till Dr. Lee recruited me.

34:39.703 --> 34:42.496
It's that simple
for you, huh?

34:43.540 --> 34:45.456
Yeah.

34:47.878 --> 34:51.297
- I should—
- You know what? Let me get these for you.

34:51.380 --> 34:54.884
- That's so cute.
- Yeah, I thought you'd like that.

34:54.967 --> 34:58.345
I did. I liked it.
But I can manage.

35:00.348 --> 35:02.808
- I have a car.
- Word?

35:02.893 --> 35:05.311
[Laila]
I can't believe I'm letting you do this.

35:05.395 --> 35:08.647
All right, um, just—
Gently.

35:08.732 --> 35:11.317
- [Tires Skid]
- [Laughing] That was not gently.

35:11.401 --> 35:13.402
- [Tires Skid]
- Okay!

35:13.486 --> 35:16.113
Okay. Okay.
I said, "gently." Hello—

35:16.198 --> 35:18.199
It's your clutch
or something.

35:18.283 --> 35:20.826
No, it's a new car.
Okay?

35:20.911 --> 35:22.536
Softly, softly. Okay?

35:24.164 --> 35:26.165
- Uh-huh.
- Not bad.

35:26.249 --> 35:28.751
Yeah. Recognize the skills.

35:31.379 --> 35:33.714
I don't even
let my sister do this.

35:33.798 --> 35:37.259
- You ain't on a date with your sister.
- This ain't a date.

35:38.511 --> 35:40.429
Snares, listen up.

35:40.513 --> 35:43.891
This last drum part
before my solo's very complicated.

35:45.977 --> 35:48.103
Pay attention.

35:50.523 --> 35:52.691
Now I'm gonna
go through it slow.

35:52.776 --> 35:54.777
Pay attention.

36:14.965 --> 36:17.091
[Sean]
Now the first game's a week away...

36:17.175 --> 36:19.969
so you're gonna have to step up
to the learning curve quick.

36:20.053 --> 36:22.137
- So take out your sheet music—
- ♪♪ [Drums]

36:31.690 --> 36:34.608
- Yeah, that'll work.
- [All Laugh]

36:34.693 --> 36:39.530
All right. Choreography formation plots
will be worked out on Wednesday.

36:39.614 --> 36:42.283
And we will have our
first run-through on Saturday.

36:42.367 --> 36:45.202
This is one of the new songs
for our first game.

36:45.287 --> 36:49.373
- It's by E.W.F. Earth, Wind & Fire.
- [Man] Old school.

36:49.457 --> 36:52.042
Come on, now.
What y'all complaining about, huh?

36:52.127 --> 36:55.838
- Oh, oh, oh, I see. Y'all think y'all a band?
- [All] Yes.

36:55.922 --> 36:58.007
Let me tell ya,
Earth, Wind & Fire was a band.

36:58.091 --> 37:00.676
- [Woman] Back in your time.
- Hold it. Hold it.

37:00.760 --> 37:04.054
- So, what y'all want to play? A little Angie Stone?
- [All] Yeah!

37:04.139 --> 37:07.141
- L.L. Cool "J"?
- [All] Yeah!

37:07.225 --> 37:10.853
- Snoop Doggy Dogg?
- [Laughing]

37:14.357 --> 37:17.526
All these artists sample
from this group, okay?

37:17.610 --> 37:20.154
That's what we gonna play.
Let's focus.

37:25.201 --> 37:27.119
One, two, ready, and—

37:27.203 --> 37:31.081
- [Man Shouting]
- ♪♪ [Rock]

38:02.906 --> 38:06.658
[Man]
♪ I found a love provides the key ♪

38:06.743 --> 38:11.038
♪ Unlocks the heart
and souls of you and me ♪

38:11.122 --> 38:14.416
♪ Love will learn
to sing your song ♪

38:14.501 --> 38:15.959
♪ Yeah ♪

38:16.044 --> 38:19.421
♪ Oh, yeah
Love is written in the stone ♪♪

38:21.966 --> 38:25.427
Before we take a break,
we have a challenge...

38:25.512 --> 38:28.013
for the Wilmington game.

38:28.098 --> 38:30.391
P3 Donnell Jones...

38:30.475 --> 38:33.310
is challenging P2 Jayson Flore...

38:33.395 --> 38:35.354
- on the basis of musicianship...
- What?

38:35.438 --> 38:37.648
and choreography.

38:37.732 --> 38:39.942
- Front and center.
- Man, that's my roommate!

38:40.026 --> 38:43.362
Shit, this is messed up.

38:43.446 --> 38:45.697
[Man]
Keep your horns up. Keep your horns up.

38:45.782 --> 38:47.866
Keep it together.
Don't flip up. Keep it together.

38:47.951 --> 38:50.244
[Dr. Lee]
Let's back him up, please.

38:50.328 --> 38:53.038
Take it from the bridge.

38:55.041 --> 38:58.710
- Hey, yo, do your thing, kid.
- [Drumsticks Clicking]

39:32.162 --> 39:34.788
[Whispering]

39:46.217 --> 39:47.843
- [Whistle Blows]
- [Man] All right, take five.

39:51.306 --> 39:55.517
Mini-Me. I need a volunteer
to polish the drums for tomorrow.

39:55.602 --> 39:59.813
- Man, that's a P4's job.
- Now I'm making it your job.

39:59.898 --> 40:02.524
You don't like it, quit.

40:23.087 --> 40:26.006
Need some help?

40:29.052 --> 40:32.054
♪♪ [Imitating Beat Box]

40:33.515 --> 40:35.432
Uh!

40:35.517 --> 40:39.478
♪♪ [Imitating Beat Box]
Uh!

40:39.562 --> 40:42.272
♪ You got me polishin' drums
till the break of dawn ♪

40:42.398 --> 40:45.692
- ♪ 'Cause some hating upperclassman
named Sean ♪
- [Laughs]

40:45.777 --> 40:48.529
♪ On and on
I'm on this drum ♪

40:48.613 --> 40:51.823
♪ And I'm tight like spandex
What I do with my hands next ♪

40:51.908 --> 40:54.826
♪ Like, check
making all the crabs cream ♪

40:54.911 --> 40:59.248
♪ This young Harlem child
put it down like bling ♪♪

40:59.332 --> 41:01.333
[Crowd Cheering]

41:04.003 --> 41:07.339
Dang, the crowd is louder than when
the football team was on the field.

41:07.423 --> 41:09.841
'Cause down here,
it's about the marching bands, dog.

41:09.926 --> 41:11.843
Halftime is game time.

41:11.928 --> 41:15.514
Percussion! Last words of advice
for our young 'uns on-line.

41:15.598 --> 41:19.309
You drop your sticks, don't reach down
and pick 'em up. Just keep moving your hands.

41:19.394 --> 41:22.729
I don't never drop my sticks.
[Chuckles]

41:22.814 --> 41:25.649
Kid, you about to step in
front of thousands of people.

41:25.733 --> 41:28.443
The crowd. The lights.
It's scary...

41:28.528 --> 41:30.779
even for a hothead like you.

41:30.863 --> 41:35.075
